# Environment Configuration

## Development Environment

```
# API Configuration
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Database
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/fivem

# JWT Secrets
JWT_SECRET=your-secret-key-here
JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=your-refresh-secret-here

# Redis (for sessions/caching)
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379

# FiveM Server Connection
FIVEM_SERVER_URL=http://localhost:30120
FIVEM_TX_ADMIN_URL=http://localhost:40120

# Logging
LOG_LEVEL=debug

# Feature Flags
ENABLE_NUI=true
ENABLE_REAL_TIME=true

# Security
ENCRYPTION_KEY=32-character-base64-encoded-key

# Email (for notifications)
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USER=your-email@gmail.com
SMTP_PASSWORD=your-app-password

# OAuth (Discord integration)
DISCORD_CLIENT_ID=your-discord-client-id
DISCORD_CLIENT_SECRET=your-discord-client-secret
DISCORD_GUILD_ID=your-discord-guild-id

# Monitoring
SENTRY_DSN=https://your-sentry-dsn@sentry.io/project-id
```

## Production Environment

```
# Same as development, but with production values
NODE_ENV=production
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://your-domain.com

# Database (RDS, CloudSQL, etc.)
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://prod_user:secure_pass_here@prod-db.example.com:5432/fivem_prod

# Redis (managed service)
REDIS_URL=redis://redis-service.example.com:6379

# Use strong, randomly generated secrets
JWT_SECRET=generate-with-openssl-rand-base64-32
JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=generate-with-openssl-rand-base64-32

# HTTPS
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.your-domain.com
```

## Local Development Setup

1. Copy this file to `.env.local`
2. Fill in all required values
3. For local development, use mock values for external services
4. Never commit `.env.local` or secrets to version control
